The 53-year-old man will spend the night behind bars after being caught speeding between George and Mossel Bay. CAPE TOWN - A motorist will spend the night behind bars after being caught driving at 170km/hour between George and Mossel Bay.The 53-year-old man was apprehended on Thursday afternoon.Provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa has again warned motorists to refrain from speeding. The man was arrested and taken to the George police station. He will appear in court on Friday for reckless and negligent driving and speeding. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)